  <refnamediv>
    <refname>install_siboot</refname>

    <refpurpose>program for installing systemimager boot tarballs</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>install_siboot </command>
      <arg choice="opt">-quiet</arg>
      <arg rep="repeat" choice="req"><replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para><command>install_siboot</command> is a utility for installing
      SystemImager boot tarballs onto your image server.</para>
    
    <refsect2>
      <title>Boot Tarballs</title>
      <para>Boot tarballs provide the files that are necessary for
        autoinstalling a particular type of client.  For example, if you need
        to autoinstall an i386 system which requires a special driver "foo",
        for use with SystemImager 2.2.0, you would download the 
        systemimager-boot-i386-foo-2.2.0.tar.bz2 file.  You would then use
        <command>install_siboot</command> to install that tarball.</para>

      <para>Official tarballs are available from 
        <ulink url="http://www.systemimager.org/pub/boot/" TYPE="alternate">
	  http://www.systemimager.org/pub/boot/</ulink>
      </para>
    </refsect2>

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>

    <para>A summary of options is included below.</para>
   
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-quiet</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
	    Don't ask any questions or print any output (other than errors).
	    In this mode, no warning will be given if the image already exists
	    on the server.
	  </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
